/-- A regular monomorphism is an isomorphism if it is an epimorphism. -/
theorem is_iso_of_regular_mono_of_epi (f : «expr ⟶ » X Y) [regular_mono f] [e : Epi f] : IsIso f :=
  is_iso_of_epi_of_strong_mono _
#align is_iso_of_regular_mono_of_epi is_iso_of_regular_mono_of_epi
is_iso_of_regular_epi_of_mono:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⟶ » -/
/-- A regular epimorphism is an isomorphism if it is a monomorphism. -/
theorem is_iso_of_regular_epi_of_mono (f : «expr ⟶ » X Y) [regular_epi f] [m : Mono f] : IsIso f :=
